Realmz but a tutorial on how to develop scenarios to be played in Realmz.  If you have no interest in actually making your own scenarios for fun and profit then read no further.                               ≈However, if the idea of making your own scenarios and maybe even distributing them as shareware is something that appeals to you then check out  the Divinity DEMO included with this copy of Realmz.                                                          ¸This TUTORIAL scenario is part of that DEMO and gives you practical examples of how to do almost anything.  Examples on how to set up battles, treasures, shops etc.  Divinity is $45 and includes a full copy of the Realmz Character Editor (a $10 value).   €Remember, you can distribute your scenarios for free -OR- you can charge a shareware fee.  If you make a cool scenario you can easily make back your purchase price of Divinity and then some by selling only a few copies.                                    ÅIf you have ever wanted to make a fantasy role playing game then don't miss your chance.  It will NEVER get any easier than this!                                                                                                                              §Code 78: Branch on Tile Parameters  This code lets you test the current tile the party is standing on and branch depending on specific traits you wish to test for.                                                                                            ˇIn this example, we will check to see if they are on Tile ID  148 which is the ID of the Well Tile below.  We will do the test below.  There is a rectangle surrounding the well.  When you walk around it will tell you if you have walked on the well or not.Not on the well                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                